      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ hemolysis validation — FDA pump benchmark",
      "description": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification over 5 flow-speed operating points. Predicted hemolysis index distributions compared against experimental measurements from the FDA generic pump dataset. The UQ campaign included one-at-a-time parameter sweeps and variance-based screening to identify dominant input contributors; these sensitivity screening results are discussed in the validation report but have not been formally linked as a structured sensitivity analysis artifact in this credibility package. Prediction intervals exceed acceptable tolerance at 3 of 5 operating points. Validation metric: normalized RMS error 0.38 (threshold 0.15). Status: insufficient for MRL 5 acceptance."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three mesh refinement levels (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.3M cells). Grid convergence index computed for hemolysis index QoI. Achieved discretization error level assessed at Gradation 2; required level for MRL 5 is Gradation 4. Gap identified."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/solver-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical solver verification against analytical and MMS solutions",
